This paper is primarily focused on the evaluation of deep learning-based face recognition algorithms, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of various evaluation metrics and APIs, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the importance of maintaining the security and privacy of biometric data, which is relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of various datasets, which is relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
